  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Some reviews have provided overviews of AI applications in infectious disease surveillance [46] [47] [48], offering vistas into the integration between AI and mechanistic models; however, a comprehensive review dedicated specifically to this integration is lacking.",
    "This scoping review aims to address this gap by systematically synthesizing literature in this emerging field.",
    "We identify solutions with the potential to address the immediate need in epidemiological modeling from various disciplines, outline the gaps between research and realworld applications, and highlight promising research directions for utilizing integrated models to provide data-driven policy guidance.",
    "Our search produced 15,460 studies (15,422 from database search, 17 through backward citation search, and 21 through manual search of relevant journals and conference proceedings).",
    "After eliminating 6267 duplicates, 9193 studies were screened."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
